				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Double attack offhand patch<a name="56498"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 12 04 10:38 PM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Procs are coded to happen a fixed number of times, they are completely independant of swings. The number of procs for offhand is basically half mainhand.
<br />

<br />
There is extensive parsing done on steelwarriors but the general rule seems to be.  2 procs / minute mainhand, 1 proc/minute offhand.  This is at 305 dex.  
<br />

<br />
The vast majority of weapons proc at this rate, some however have a lower or higher proc rate.  E.g.  AHB proc rate is 103%, i.e. higher  Riwi Mace has no rate modifier.
<br />

<br />
This is the accepted wisdom taken from extensive parses... HOWEVER.  I have heard stories of warriors AE'ing with that Earthshaker weapon, and they use a shammy to slow themselves as they claim it raises proc rate.  Go figure....
<br />

<br />
Melo</span></td>
