			<tr>
				<td class="PanelBodyAlternate"><span class="SmallBoldText">Re: Double attack offhand patch<a name="56510"/></span><br><span class="SmallText"> Posted: </span><span class="SmallText">Aug 13 04 3:19 AM</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span>Proc rate is coded based upon fixed number of procs per minute, but I beileve that the number of swings comes into play as a % chance of a proc based upon the fixed rate.  For example, if you have a weapon with a 60 delay (ie 1 swing/tick or 10 swings/min), with a max proc chances of 2/min, that would translate to a 20% chance of a proc per swing.  The fixed rate is not absolute - you often see multiple procs within a short amount of time -- but simply represents the average.  That is one reason haste does not increase the proc rate, and the actual chance to proc per swing decreases!
<br />

<br />
So all things being equal, a slower delay weapon has a better chance to proc per swing than a faster weapon as it still is trying to proc 2/min.  With Earthshaker and a slow, you increase the proc rate per swing tremendously, and when you are attacking everything that swings at you using an aa ability, and you have 40-60 mobs attacking you, you will proc a huge number of times.  Given that Earthshaker is a pbaoe proc, that is the warrior's ghetto pbaoe method.  There are a number of threads on Steel Warriors about 3-4 Earthshaker equipped warriors taking on almost entire PoP zones for huge aa gains.  Of course, the warriiors all died, but their group mates were the beneficiaries of their sacrifice.</span></td>
			</tr><tr>
				<td colspan="2"><span class="SmallText"></span></td>
			</tr><tr>
